path.id: Escape the ordinary and delve into the misty embrace of Sri Lanka's Knuckles Mountain Range. This UNESCO World Heritage Site, named for its resemblance to a clenched fist, is a tapestry of emerald valleys, cascading waterfalls, and biodiverse rainforests. Hike through ancient tea plantations, spot playful monkeys in the canopy, and bathe in the cool spray of hidden waterfalls. In the Knuckles, every bend unveils a breathtaking panorama, whispering tales of forgotten kingdoms and timeless beauty.
